commentTextItems.html: all over! Shakib makes room and punches another full ball over the infield and Bangladesh have leveled the series at 1-1 in front of a raucous home crowd

commentPostTextItems.html: Good win for Bangladesh. They were the better side by some distance. Razzak led the way with 5 for 29 and Shakib finished it off in Raqibul's company with a flamboyant century. The crowd laps it up as he walks off. This is a big win, with seven wickets and 123 balls remaining. A target of 220 just didn't test Bangladesh. Razzak and Shakib will now vie for the Man-of-the-Match award. Stay tuned.
Zaman: "Yes! This guy Shakib is the number 1 all-rounder! Not only in Bangladesh but in the world also. Bangladesh need more players like him. They don't need a talent like Ash!"
Abul Shamsuddin: "We need a player like Ashraful. Unfortunatly, he is going through a bad patch. Don't discount him alltogether."
Asif Rahman: "Agree with Zaman. Ash has to go. We have more consistent players in the dugout, aching to go."
Masakadza: "We started well but it turned out to be a bad day in the office. We just didn't get enough runs. We need more runs. The wicket played very well."

Shakib: "Very happy that we came back so well. Razzak bowled very well and I got some runs. They started well after ten overs and we were worried but we knew our strength was spin and that worked. Ashraful is a key bowler and every time he comes on he gets wickets. We're looking forward to the rest of the series."

Razzak is the Man of the Match: "I'm very happy. In morning time we were on the back foot when they began well but we came back well. There wasn't that much turn but I focused to put the ball on the stumps."
So that is it from us at Cricinfo. See you next time. Bye for now!

commentTextItems.html: and there it is! Hundred No. 4 for Shakib! The crowd comes to its feet as Shakib reaches out and squeezes a wide ball down to third man and brings up three figures, it has been a very good innings from the captain

commentPreTextItems.html: Right then. Shakib needs three. Bangladesh need seven. The crowd is abuzz.

commentTextItems.html: good ball, cramps him for room with the length and Shakib gets up to punch the ball out to the deep, its an easy single but they have a good think before taking it and decide not to in the end
once again he just defends to ensure Shakib gets to face

commentTextItems.html: full outside off, Shakib moves to 97 with a punch to extra cover

commentPostTextItems.html: Zohaib: "This guy shakib looks like a very talented player. There is no doubt in my mind that he is the best cricketer that bangladesh has ever produced. Scores runs and takes wickets consistently yet it all goes unnoticed, no wonder he is not playing IPL yet!"

commentTextItems.html: comes dancing out to try and throw the bowler off line, swats at a short ball and just mistimes it wide of mid-on, Waller runs in from long-on and dives but the ball drops short and ricochets away
nice and straight, Shakib backs away but cannot beat cover

commentPreTextItems.html: Shakib on 94 .. on the leg side there are three men right on the ropes ... on the off side there are five on the circle

commentTextItems.html: short of a length, he goes back and punches to cover
short of a length, he opens the face and steers it to third man

commentPostTextItems.html: There's a clear plan here ... Raqibul has been told to just get singles

commentTextItems.html: slow bouncer outside off and Raqibul ducks, wide called for height
nice ball again, very full in the blockhole and punched back

bang, that's four! In the slot to be driven outside off and Shakib punches it fiercely back past the bowler
short, too slow, sits up nicely and Shakib pulls over midwicket
shorter ball on middle and off, he gets up and turns it away for one

dismissalText.commentary: Hamilton Masakadza lbw b Naeem Islam 34 (31b 5x4 1x6 45m) SR: 109.67

dismissalComment.html: first breakthrough for Bangladesh, Masakadza sweeps and the ball strikes the pad outside the line, loud shout and given, the batsman is unlucky.

headshotImage.longCaption: Mohammad Ashraful player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha st †Mushfiqur Rahim b Mohammad Ashraful 39 (67b 5x4 0x6 79m) SR: 58.2

dismissalComment.html: quicker delivery outside the off stump and Chibhabha playing forward gets beaten by the straight delivery and drags his feet from the crease and Rahim does the rest, gets rid of the bails. Good knock from Chibhabha comes to an end.

headshotImage.caption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Brendan Taylor b Abdur Razzak 21 (29b 2x4 0x6 36m) SR: 72.41

dismissalComment.html: lovely delivery from Razzak, pitches on the leg stump and knocks the top of off stump, Taylor does not play for the turn and gets beaten.

dismissalText.long: c Junaid Siddique b Abdur Razzak
dismissalText.commentary: Charles Coventry c Junaid Siddique b Abdur Razzak 0 (4b 0x4 0x6 3m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: another one bites the dust, the spinners are on top, pitches on the stump and spins across, the ball takes the edge and Junaid Siddiqui at first slip takes the catch on his second attempt.

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Matsikenyeri c †Mushfiqur Rahim b Mohammad Ashraful 14 (29b 1x4 0x6 33m) SR: 48.27

dismissalComment.html: gone! This time Rahim picks the edge as Matsikenyeri edges a fuller delivery to Rahim, who makes no mistakes this time

dismissalText.long: c Raqibul Hasan b Naeem Islam
dismissalText.commentary: Tatenda Taibu c Raqibul Hasan b Naeem Islam 38 (56b 1x4 1x6 84m) SR: 67.85

dismissalComment.html: was that a lapse in concentration or sheer tiredness as Taibu reaches out for the delivery and deposits it straight into the hands of the fielder, Raqibul at deep midwicket. He was looking good for some more runs but then...

headshotImage.caption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Malcolm Waller b Abdur Razzak 40 (39b 4x4 1x6 60m) SR: 102.56

dismissalComment.html: lovely delivery from Razzak, pitches on the leg stump and turns to take the off and middle, as Waller plays down the wrong line.

headshotImage.caption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Abdur Razzak player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Graeme Cremer b Abdur Razzak 2 (9b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 22.22

dismissalComment.html: and strikes the timber with an arm-ball. Cremer was looking to cut it away and is beaten by the bounce. He would have been better off playing straight of all the three balls in the over. What's the use of crying over split milk

dismissalText.long: c Mahmudullah b Shakib Al Hasan
dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c Mahmudullah b Shakib Al Hasan 8 (14b 0x4 0x6 29m) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: and Chigumbara is gone! Frustrated by the lack of runs in the powerplay, he decides to take the aerial route and only manages a leading edge to Mahmudullah at mid-ff. Shakib is ecstatic

dismissalText.commentary: Kyle Jarvis lbw b Abdur Razzak 0 (2b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: five-for there! Razzaq gets one right in front of the middle stump and traps Jarvis right in front and he is brimming with joy as he gets his second five wicket haul and he knows it

dismissalText.commentary: Tamim Iqbal c Masakadza b Chibhabha 26 (19b 2x4 1x6 35m) SR: 136.84

dismissalComment.html: now this is sheer irresponsibility on part of Tamim as he looks to pull a short delivery and gets a top edge, which is taken comfortably by Masakadza at mid-off. He will be in for a dressing down from the people who matter
